No one on the staff, no one knows that this will be done.

94
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:41,680
I do not know the details myself, but now I'm going to be hacked.

95
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:45,680
"Good luck." But not too much "luck".

96
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:51,480
We at Langate know that we may be the victim of a hacker attack -

97
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:54,640
-To access our customers.

98
00:09:54,800 --> 00:10:00,720
- We want to create as good protection as we can. -Because you become the most sensitive part.

99
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:06,520
Yes, we will be the service provider supply chain to others.

100
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:09,960
Potentially, one could reach–

101
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:14,520
-About a hundred customers important information.

102
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:20,880
-Or make do ransomware attack ... -Some kind of malicious code.

103
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:27,440
Or just access information that you see has an incredible business value.

104
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:38,440
I had an experience this weekend. A customer who has refused protection -

105
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:42,080
-And insist that we publish our terminal server.

106
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:49,040
Then they got ransomware, and boom the pay system stopped working. Nasty!

107
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:54,360
Ransomware is a billion dollar industry. It will only get bigger.

108
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:59,640
Swedish companies that are attacked by ransomware and pays ...

109
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:05,640
The total amount per year amounts to several billion SEK.

110
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:11,000
There are cases where Swedish companies has paid close to 300 million–

111
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:15,560
-To get their files unlocked. And that is ONE company.

112
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:22,760
A hacker who accessed resources can perform a ransomware attack.

113
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:26,680
What happens is that all files are encrypted and locked.

114
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:30,760
Now a key is required to restore everything.

115
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:37,080
The files were hijacked by the hacker, who demands money to unlock.

116
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:43,440
The Coop food chain had to close almost all of its 800 stores.

117
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:46,320
-After the cash register system failed.

118
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:50,640
This summer, Coop was hit by a ransomware attack-

119
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:53,680
-Which was also a supply chain attack.

120
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:58,320
Operation of Coop's cash register system is handled by the company Visma Esscom.

121
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:03,440
Visma in turn uses services from the company Kaseya.

122
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:07,200
It was Kaseya who was attacked by a hacker.

123
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:13,720
The malicious code was spread to Visma and caused Coop's cash registers to be locked.

124
00:12:13,880 --> 00:12:20,600
Coop had to close 800 stores while they restarted all cash registers manually.

125
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:27,520
There are more examples of attacks which affected companies and infrastructure.

126
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:31,560
2019 the aluminium manufacturer Norsk Hydro was affected.

127
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:36,080
It was enough for an employee to click on a link in an email.

128
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:40,720
The hackers entered Hydro's IT environment and planted a virus–

129
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:45,480
-Which they used to encrypt information throughout the company.

130
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:50,280
Computers and servers were locked and production lines stopped.

131
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:55,240
The total sum for the attack estimated at $ 75 million.

132
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:58,520
Norsk Hydro never paid any ransom.

133
00:12:58,680 --> 00:13:04,720
They had backups on their data and was able to restart operations.

134
00:13:04,880 --> 00:13:11,600
Sensitive information about bank vaults, alarms systems and the government is online.

135
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:18,520
The security company Gunnebo was hit by a ransomware attack in 2020.

136
00:13:18,680 --> 00:13:24,560
Gunnebo refused to pay the ransom. About 38,000 documents were leaked -

137
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:27,280
and are exposed online.

138
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:31,680
drawings of bank vaults, alarm systems and sensitive facilities.

139
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:37,680
In a survey among 150 IT-managers at Swedish companies -

140
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:44,040
- 30% state that they've been exposed to one ransomware attack in the last year.

141
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:57,680
Here we go. Let's do it.

142
00:13:57,840 --> 00:14:03,200
-Now we're on our way. How nice! -It's fun to watch it.

143
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:07,920
Hey! I'm here to measure some moisture in your walls.

144
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:12,240
- From Sölvesborgs Construction, or? -Yes. Or from Sölvesborg municipality.

145
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:15,680
I checked under the sink and so on.

146
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:22,920
- Moist tile, then?. -Yeah, what the hell do I know?

147
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:29,360
In an attack like this, you don't know how prepared the victim is.

148
00:14:29,520 --> 00:14:34,720
So you need to do it slowly and carefully, so that you do not ...

149
00:14:34,880 --> 00:14:39,840
You don't want to make too much noise in the network.

150
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:45,480
You don't know what to expect. It's a bit like a maze without a map.

151
00:14:45,640 --> 00:14:52,040
You have a bunch of cool tools, but there are monsters in the maze.

152
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:58,360
- No password spraying, just. -No no no.

153
00:14:59,520 --> 00:15:04,040
Come on...! I Having some issues here.

