They found it?

207
00:20:06,360 --> 00:20:11,160
After a while our terminal freeze–

208
00:20:11,320 --> 00:20:17,960
- and we lose the connection to our unit that sits on the inside.

209
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:21,120
Yes, I'm all out.

210
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:28,560
- Damn. We were too aggressive. -Yes, you can probably say that.

211
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:35,520
They find our box and disconnect it. We lose the connection. Game over.

212
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:46,360
Now that we are blind again and have no access, we have a few hashes.

213
00:20:46,520 --> 00:20:52,040
The hashes are the cryptographic equivalent of a password.

214
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:56,640
And we can crack these using computing power.

215
00:20:56,800 --> 00:21:03,520
Powerful computers with graphics cards which we ask to solve our problem.

216
00:21:06,960 --> 00:21:13,640
Time is running out. While Linus is trying to crack passwords

217
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:17,520
- Jinny and Jesper go back to the company office.

218
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:21,600
It's time to reveal ourselves.

219
00:21:21,760 --> 00:21:26,560
We'll see what they answer, if they have noticed anything.

220
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:32,000
-Welcome! -Thank you. - After you.

221
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:35,640
-Are you having a good time? -Yes.

222
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:43,680
We have some friends with us, me and my colleague:

223
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:47,200
Jinny, or Frida.

224
