00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:46,240
Then I recognize Jinny, who has infiltrated us.

236
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:50,000
I'm the one who opens the door.

237
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:54,720
Hey! I'm here to measure some moisture in your walls.

238
00:22:54,880 --> 00:23:00,800
-What did we do here, quite simply? -You were measuring moi ...

239
00:23:05,840 --> 00:23:09,920
It was a very positive reaction. I was afraid he would get angry.

240
00:23:10,080 --> 00:23:14,880
But he laughed and ... So there's shock, but laughter, as well.

241
00:23:15,040 --> 00:23:19,960
I'm in a call when I open the door. I'm talking to a customer about security.

242
00:23:20,120 --> 00:23:23,360
I say, "The doorbell rings."

243
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:28,240
"Hi, my name is Frida I'm going to measure moisture. "-" Yes, go ahead. "

244
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:32,120
"It's very important, with security! "

245
00:23:34,040 --> 00:23:38,320
But you haven't noticed anything on infrastructure or ...?

246
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:45,040
We noticed a response on the computer, which did not feel natural.

247
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:48,200
What's supposed to happen doesn't happen–

248
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:52,640
- instead we get a  login box. That's weird.

249
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:58,600
We have seen a small box in a room which you may have put there.

250
00:23:58,760 --> 00:24:02,280
I suspect that it's no longer connected.

251
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:08,080
-How did you find it? -A colleague of mine saw it.

252
00:24:08,240 --> 00:24:14,680
In reality, one of our customers was attacked for real.

253
00:24:14,840 --> 00:24:19,840
So Jörgen and I request  people to come here, and tell them:

254
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:24,320
"Now we have prio 1 alert. Someone has been hacked. "

255
00:24:24,480 --> 00:24:27,480
Pretty strange, weird timing.

256
00:24:27,640 --> 00:24:31,560
They had another incident at the same time.

257
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:35,200
A customer had an intrusion while we were doing stuff.

258
00:24:35,360 --> 00:24:39,120
"I see a box. Do you know anything about it?"

259
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:43,840
"No. No idea what internal project is this? "

260
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:46,440
"Then I want to disconnect it."

261
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:51,520
We could have stayed in the network longer if they did not have the incident.

262
00:24:51,680 --> 00:24:54,440
So that was just unfortunate.

263
00:24:55,520 --> 00:25:01,760
People have lost three years of work because they've been attacked.

264
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:08,320
They attacked the data, but also the backup of the data. Then it's gone.

265
00:25:08,480 --> 00:25:13,040
Then you cry for real. You've worked for three years–

266
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:16,600
-for nothing and have to start over.

267
00:25:16,760 --> 00:25:20,280
There is nothing to recreate or save.

268
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:25,480
We have taken two passwords and given them to our machines.

269
00:25:25,640 --> 00:25:30,800
They're cracking the password still. It's not cracked yet.

270
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:38,200
We have had a very short time - we have spent almost two days on planning.

271
00:25:38,360 --> 00:25:42,520
It's just a matter of time before this gets cracked.

272
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:46,600
We got our hands on two encrypted passwords - hashes.

273
00:25:46,760 --> 00:25:52,840
We have tried to crack them for 24 hours and have not succeeded yet.

274
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:57,560
It's sad for us, but a good grade for Langate.

275
00:25:57,720 --> 00:26:01,920
In my world you have succeeded, even if you don't think so.

276
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:05,320
The hackers managed to infiltrate the IT company–

277
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:10,080
-And had access to their network for over a day.

278
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:14,880
They could not get past the company's security system -

279
00:26:15,040 --> 00:26:18,840
-And therefore could not access the customers in the network.

280
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:23,200
The passwords that the hackers came across kept good quality.

281
00:26:23,360 --> 00:26:27,680
Attempts to crack them were discontinued after 48 hours.

282
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:31,200
They remain unresolved.

283
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:37,280
If I were an evil hacker, I'd be quieter–

284
00:26:37,440 --> 00:26:41,800
- and take my time. When I had enough customers -

285
00:26:41,960 --> 00:26:45,520
- I'd probably encrypt everything–

286
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:48,680
-And requested loads of money in ransom.

287
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:54,160
If they don't pay, yeah, go bankrupt, then.

288
00:26:54,320 --> 00:26:56,840
"What do I care? I'm evil."

289
00:27:03,480 --> 00:27:07,880
We currently don't have a basic level of security -

290
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:12,080
-So that we have a fairly high bar. The higher the bar is–

291
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:16,480
-The more costly and time consuming it is for an attacker-

292
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:23,480
- to try to access the information. This is business-critical.

293
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:29,000
This is what boards should be accustomed to dealing with.

294
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:33,000
You see investments in security as a cost.

295
00:27:33,160 --> 00:27:37,480
If you see it as an investment, something that gives a return–

296
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:44,640
-it's easier to argue for. It's about the company's survival.

297
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:51,480
This has to end now. I'm tired of talking to desperate people -

298
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:57,400
-who get in trouble because of hacker attacks all the time.

299
00:28:03,320 --> 00:28:09,320
Good morning, Klara. Hope you have slept well. Today it's sunny outside.

300
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:14,400
This so-called IoT man is like a damn mad scientist.

301
00:28:14,560 --> 00:28:17,720
I'm safe, they're not getting in.

302
00:28:17,880 --> 00:28:21,880
-Check if you get access. -It's up, we're in.

